snippet: U.S. voters in 14 states are navigating new laws that critics say make it harder for lower-income and minority voters, who typically back Democrats, to cast ballots in the midterm elections....

headline.print_headline: U.S. Voters Contend With New Voting Rules in 14 States
headline.main: U.S. Voters Contend With New Voting Rules in 14 States

lead_paragraph: U.S. voters in 14 states are navigating new laws that critics say make it harder for lower-income and minority voters, who typically back Democrats, to cast ballots in the midterm elections.
